1
00:00:05,696 --> 00:00:08,392
<i>Press down hard on the gas</i>

2
00:00:08,465 --> 00:00:12,333
<i>That's right, there's no compromise</i>

3
00:00:12,403 --> 00:00:16,396
<i>We'll slip through the night</i>

4
00:00:16,740 --> 00:00:19,231
<i>At the final moment push hard</i>

5
00:00:19,310 --> 00:00:23,371
<i>That's right, all the way to zero,</i>

6
00:00:23,447 --> 00:00:27,406
<i>Until we wipe away the days</i>

7
00:00:28,886 --> 00:00:33,619
<i>Gently open your heart</i>

8
00:00:34,325 --> 00:00:37,294
<i>If you pull it close to you</i>

9
00:00:39,730 --> 00:00:41,823
<i>It will reach you, without a doubt</i>

10
00:00:42,566 --> 00:00:43,863
<i>It will come, closer</i>

11
00:00:44,201 --> 00:00:46,761
<i>Now</i>

12
00:00:54,812 --> 00:01:00,182
<i>We're speeding through life,</i>
<i>squeezing it for all of its worth</i>

13
00:01:00,384 --> 00:01:01,544
<i>Our feet are tied</i>

14
00:01:01,618 --> 00:01:05,418
<i>But we still keep going farther</i>

15
00:01:05,756 --> 00:01:10,955
<i>Even if I take it back, and grasp it</i>

16
00:01:11,228 --> 00:01:12,559
<i>If you're not the one</i>

17
00:01:12,629 --> 00:01:14,028
<i>There will be no meaning</i>

18
00:01:14,098 --> 00:01:20,367
<i>And so we'll go far off into the distance.</i>

19
00:01:44,247 --> 00:01:45,407
Special technique!

20
00:01:46,249 --> 00:01:48,444
Shadow Clone Jutsu, fishing version!

21
00:02:12,308 --> 00:02:13,570
Thrash about more!

22
00:02:13,710 --> 00:02:15,200
I want to catch some for curing!

23
00:02:15,445 --> 00:02:16,707
Three isn't enough!

24
00:02:18,281 --> 00:02:20,249
Three more, you loser!

25
00:02:22,452 --> 00:02:25,387
This is very taxing, you know?!

26
00:02:25,455 --> 00:02:26,319
I mean, let's switch!

27
00:02:26,656 --> 00:02:27,623
Sasuke!

28
00:02:28,892 --> 00:02:31,554
The fire's ready to light!
Fireballs please.

29
00:02:34,097 --> 00:02:35,826
I guess three is okay for the time being...

30
00:02:36,466 --> 00:02:37,194
Wha?

31
00:02:38,401 --> 00:02:40,528
Hey, wait a minute!

32
00:02:40,603 --> 00:02:46,439
<i>The Scroll's Secret.</i>
<i>No Peeking Allowed</i>

33
00:02:49,646 --> 00:02:52,615
It's already been four days
since the second exam started.

34
00:02:53,316 --> 00:02:53,805
Yeah.

35
00:02:54,417 --> 00:02:55,042
That's right.

36
00:02:56,386 --> 00:02:59,219
The start of the second exam
was around three in the afternoon.

37
00:03:00,089 --> 00:03:02,319
We only have twenty-five or
twenty-six. Hours left.

38
00:03:03,426 --> 00:03:06,190
There may already be
some teams that have passed.

39
00:03:06,863 --> 00:03:07,693
That means...

40
00:03:09,832 --> 00:03:11,732
<i>I wonder if it'll be broiled soon.</i>

41
00:03:13,169 --> 00:03:16,195
<i>We're soon going to be in a hot spot...</i>

42
00:03:18,308 --> 00:03:20,333
<i>That's the biggest one.</i>

43
00:03:20,410 --> 00:03:21,399
<i>Believe it!</i>

44
00:03:22,378 --> 00:03:23,538
<i>Okay...</i>

45
00:03:27,317 --> 00:03:28,215
Even if we were to try pursuit,

46
00:03:28,284 --> 00:03:30,980
there's probably hardly anybody left
to become targets.

47
00:03:31,354 --> 00:03:32,218
What do we do?

48
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:40,254
Almost everyone's surely already passed.

49
00:03:40,697 --> 00:03:43,165
Yeah. It's already been
four days, after all.

50
00:03:44,834 --> 00:03:45,823
Anyway...

51
00:03:46,035 --> 00:03:46,933
It's early afternoon now...

52
00:03:47,003 --> 00:03:48,163
Let's have a meal.

53
00:03:52,008 --> 00:03:55,637
You two rest a bit and
I'll go find us something to eat.

54
00:04:02,585 --> 00:04:03,779
Say...

55
00:04:04,354 --> 00:04:05,082
Hmm?

56
00:04:05,822 --> 00:04:07,722
As I recall, on the other one...

57
00:04:08,224 --> 00:04:11,284
"Heaven" was written here...

58
00:04:11,494 --> 00:04:16,056
and unlike this,
both edges of the scroll were whitish, right?

59
00:04:16,299 --> 00:04:19,564
Umm, when I was shown
the scroll before the exam,

60
00:04:19,636 --> 00:04:21,570
I wasn't really looking.

61
00:04:22,271 --> 00:04:24,899
So, what of it all of a sudden?

62
00:04:29,212 --> 00:04:31,442
Y-You've got to be kidding...?

63
00:04:41,057 --> 00:04:42,251
For all we know...

64
00:04:43,626 --> 00:04:46,117
there may not be any Heaven scrolls.

65
00:04:46,929 --> 00:04:48,487
What do you mean, Sakura?

66
00:04:48,931 --> 00:04:50,922
Well, in this second exam...

67
00:04:51,501 --> 00:04:55,130
four of the five day
time limit have passed already.

68
00:04:55,905 --> 00:05:00,035
So that means we've already
used eighty percent of the total exam time.

69
00:05:00,743 --> 00:05:03,678
Seventy eight participants
and twenty six teams.

70
00:05:04,247 --> 00:05:06,909
There are only thirteen each
of the Heaven and Earth scrolls.

71
00:05:07,116 --> 00:05:10,210
At most there are only
thirteen passing teams.

72
00:05:11,988 --> 00:05:14,786
Moreover, you remember,
don't you, Sasuke?

73
00:05:17,727 --> 00:05:22,892
That the Orochimaru guy burned
the " Heaven scroll that we had.

74
00:05:24,867 --> 00:05:25,993
Which means...

75
00:05:26,869 --> 00:05:31,101
The teams that will pass had already,
at that point, decreased by one.

76
00:05:31,174 --> 00:05:31,833
Hmm?

77
00:05:32,608 --> 00:05:36,806
Also, all of the other scrolls are
not necessarily safe, so...

78
00:05:40,717 --> 00:05:42,412
After parting ways with
the leaf Village bunch,

79
00:05:42,485 --> 00:05:44,976
we allotted two days for healing...

80
00:05:46,089 --> 00:05:49,058
So from here on, we have to increase
the distance of our actions.

81
00:05:50,460 --> 00:05:55,056
At any rate,
the next enemy is our last chance.

82
00:05:57,066 --> 00:05:58,533
I'm going to get some drinking water.

83
00:06:12,849 --> 00:06:14,510
Say! Say!

84
00:06:15,351 --> 00:06:18,149
I have a good way for us not to fight
with an enemy. Believe it!

85
00:06:18,454 --> 00:06:19,250
What?!

86
00:06:23,693 --> 00:06:24,591
Get serious!

87
00:06:24,961 --> 00:06:26,553
I am serious.

88
00:06:26,863 --> 00:06:29,957
I have lots of scrolls stocked, so.

89
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:33,763
Ninjutsu manual, deadly poison manual,
for notes...

90
00:06:33,903 --> 00:06:37,168
If we tweak this a little and change it
into exactly like the Heaven scroll...

91
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:38,639
H-Hold it!

92
00:06:38,808 --> 00:06:39,570
Huh?

93
00:06:39,842 --> 00:06:43,243
Even if you did such a thing
you don't know what's written on the inside!

94
00:06:43,713 --> 00:06:46,273
If the Proctor looked inside
you will be discovered right away!

95
00:06:46,382 --> 00:06:47,110
Idiot!

96
00:06:47,784 --> 00:06:49,411
Generally with things like this,

97
00:06:49,485 --> 00:06:51,453
there's a password or
something written

98
00:06:51,521 --> 00:06:54,581
and you can't get it
unless you have both scrolls.

99
00:06:55,525 --> 00:06:56,787
In other words...

100
00:06:56,859 --> 00:07:00,386
to pass at the tower goal,
we'll surely need a password.

101
00:07:00,463 --> 00:07:02,397
Or something like that.
Believe it!

102
00:07:02,899 --> 00:07:04,833
What difference does it make?

103
00:07:05,668 --> 00:07:09,832
If you don't know the content,
there's no use making a fake!

104
00:07:13,442 --> 00:07:16,639
Man, here I was wondering what
you were going to say, looking all big...

105
00:07:17,413 --> 00:07:19,108
You're an idiot who just can't
think through things.

106
00:07:20,049 --> 00:07:21,141
B-But...

107
00:07:21,450 --> 00:07:24,180
What if we could predict the content...?

108
00:07:25,755 --> 00:07:26,915
This Earth scroll...

109
00:07:27,223 --> 00:07:28,281
You wouldn't...

110
00:07:29,292 --> 00:07:33,126
I'm going to... open this scroll!

111
00:07:33,196 --> 00:07:34,220
No!

112
00:07:35,031 --> 00:07:37,761
You! Have you forgotten
even the rules, you idiot?

113
00:07:38,267 --> 00:07:42,169
We were told not to look inside the scrolls
until arriving at the tower, right?

114
00:07:42,371 --> 00:07:45,397
But, at this rate,
we'll be in a hot spot, right?

115
00:08:20,743 --> 00:08:22,335
There might be a trap or something.

116
00:08:23,145 --> 00:08:25,306
Carefully... Be careful.

117
00:08:26,015 --> 00:08:26,777
Yeah.

118
00:08:27,617 --> 00:08:28,811
I know...

119
00:09:36,552 --> 00:09:37,951
Hey, what's wrong?

120
00:09:38,754 --> 00:09:39,311
Hey!

121
00:09:47,163 --> 00:09:47,891
What's wrong?

122
00:09:48,264 --> 00:09:49,026
What happened?!

123
00:09:49,332 --> 00:09:49,957
Hey!

124
00:09:55,638 --> 00:09:57,503
Hey!
Answer me!

125
00:10:34,929 --> 00:10:35,918
You'd best not do it.

126
00:10:44,472 --> 00:10:45,370
<i>An enemy?</i>

127
00:10:53,415 --> 00:10:55,474
Man, you're beyond saving...

128
00:10:56,484 --> 00:10:57,746
That was close.

129
00:10:58,219 --> 00:11:00,016
W-We're sorry.

130
00:11:02,090 --> 00:11:06,754
Those who ignored the rules are forced
into the situation of having to retire.

131
00:11:07,395 --> 00:11:10,831
In the previous exam, hypnotism
Jutsu Formula was set up to

132
00:11:10,899 --> 00:11:14,027
get into the eyes of those who looked
at the scroll along the way.

133
00:11:15,170 --> 00:11:19,368
A measure to get them to lie
in the forest until the end of the exam.

134
00:11:21,509 --> 00:11:22,669
By the way...

135
00:11:22,744 --> 00:11:24,735
If I'm not mistaken, you're Kabuto, right?

136
00:11:25,313 --> 00:11:27,781
What're you doing hanging
around here alone?

137
00:11:28,216 --> 00:11:31,549
It's not that I'm after your scroll.

138
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:32,846
I didn't think so.

139
00:11:33,121 --> 00:11:37,524
If that was your intention...
you could've taken it from Naruto just now.

140
00:11:38,793 --> 00:11:41,557
So you're also after the Heaven scroll?

141
00:11:41,963 --> 00:11:42,725
No.

142
00:11:43,331 --> 00:11:45,094
I already have them both.

143
00:11:46,201 --> 00:11:46,826
See?

144
00:11:47,335 --> 00:11:48,131
<i>What?</i>

145
00:11:49,003 --> 00:11:50,493
Things led to things...

146
00:11:50,638 --> 00:11:52,538
I was hurrying over to
the vicinity of the tower

147
00:11:52,607 --> 00:11:54,302
to wait for my estranged companions.

148
00:11:55,310 --> 00:11:57,278
Now, if you'll excuse me...

149
00:11:59,781 --> 00:12:00,679
Wait!

150
00:12:04,519 --> 00:12:05,349
Fight me.

151
00:12:11,126 --> 00:12:12,024
Lucky!

152
00:12:14,195 --> 00:12:15,127
Fight you, you say?

153
00:12:16,131 --> 00:12:17,155
S-Sasuke.

154
00:12:17,232 --> 00:12:18,392
This idiot suke.

155
00:12:18,466 --> 00:12:19,956
What are you saying suddenly?

156
00:12:20,702 --> 00:12:21,600
Are you serious?

157
00:12:22,570 --> 00:12:26,370
Sorry, but we don't have anymore time.

158
00:12:26,841 --> 00:12:30,971
Hey, Sasuke!
Kabuto saved us!

159
00:12:31,413 --> 00:12:34,780
Sasuke, I don't know about that, myself.

160
00:12:34,983 --> 00:12:35,813
Shut up!

161
00:12:36,885 --> 00:12:38,147
Sasu... ke.

162
00:12:38,987 --> 00:12:42,184
It can't be helped.
I said it before, too.

163
00:12:42,690 --> 00:12:46,182
This is all that can be done
to survive through this forest now.

164
00:12:46,528 --> 00:12:49,122
Hmm... That's a lie.

165
00:12:51,199 --> 00:12:51,927
A lie?

166
00:12:52,734 --> 00:12:56,636
Your heart isn't totally in this
as much as you're saying.

167
00:12:58,973 --> 00:13:02,704
If you could really become
serious about this exam...

168
00:13:03,344 --> 00:13:05,642
Why is it necessary to fight me?

169
00:13:07,348 --> 00:13:09,509
You should jump on me
at my unguarded moment,

170
00:13:09,584 --> 00:13:12,314
without going to
the trouble of announcing it.

171
00:13:13,188 --> 00:13:15,850
That's... a Ninja.

172
00:13:17,826 --> 00:13:20,852
Hmm, that's profound.

173
00:13:22,096 --> 00:13:24,155
I don't dislike that side of you.

174
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:29,261
So I shall tell you the way you should go.

175
00:13:30,371 --> 00:13:33,397
However... let's talk as we move.

176
00:13:33,842 --> 00:13:37,778
The smell of broiled fish in the fire smoke
had reached a great distance.

177
00:13:38,079 --> 00:13:41,207
At this rate, we'll be marked
by fierce animals... and enemies.

178
00:13:48,089 --> 00:13:49,078
Humph!

179
00:13:56,231 --> 00:13:58,222
Are there really still enemies around?

180
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:00,329
Yes, no mistake.

181
00:14:00,735 --> 00:14:02,293
If you think about it a little,
you'll understand.

182
00:14:03,872 --> 00:14:07,000
Do you know the cleverest way
of fighting in battles

183
00:14:07,075 --> 00:14:09,669
in jungles and
expansive forests such as this?

184
00:14:10,378 --> 00:14:11,174
No.

185
00:14:11,646 --> 00:14:13,739
The tower located in the center
of this forest,

186
00:14:13,815 --> 00:14:15,908
the common goal for us test-takers.

187
00:14:16,484 --> 00:14:18,884
That means when the last day
of the test is here...

188
00:14:18,953 --> 00:14:24,084
the area near that tower is
the easiest place to gather scrolls.

189
00:14:24,692 --> 00:14:27,160
Oh, I see.
Ambush, right?

190
00:14:27,495 --> 00:14:29,793
In other words, we go after the scrolls
of the teams

191
00:14:29,864 --> 00:14:33,823
that have both the Heaven and Earth scrolls
and are setting out for the tower.

192
00:14:34,802 --> 00:14:36,167
That's one third of the answer.

193
00:14:36,404 --> 00:14:37,200
What?

194
00:14:37,338 --> 00:14:40,330
I mean that you guys are
not the only ones thinking that!

195
00:14:41,142 --> 00:14:45,135
Near the tower, the same badgers
have probably already set traps, so...

196
00:14:45,446 --> 00:14:46,344
I see!

197
00:14:46,414 --> 00:14:50,510
That means there are lots of enemies
lying in wait to engage us.

198
00:14:51,252 --> 00:14:54,847
Heh, having a handicap
gets me pumped, I say!

199
00:14:55,123 --> 00:14:56,283
I'm looking forward to it!

200
00:14:56,491 --> 00:14:59,824
If we just beat them all and
get the Heaven scroll,

201
00:14:59,894 --> 00:15:02,158
we'll all survive the second exam!

202
00:15:02,297 --> 00:15:04,822
No! This is still two-thirds of the answer!

203
00:15:05,066 --> 00:15:07,125
What's the remaining
one third of the answer?

204
00:15:07,902 --> 00:15:11,201
The collectors who are certain
to appear during an exam of this nature.

205
00:15:11,573 --> 00:15:12,938
Collectors?

206
00:15:13,675 --> 00:15:15,643
In this exam, with the tower
just a stone's throw away,

207
00:15:15,710 --> 00:15:17,644
you definitely can't rest easy...

208
00:15:18,746 --> 00:15:21,078
Those particular conditions
are what create them.

209
00:15:21,916 --> 00:15:25,477
In other words,
those who gather extra scrolls...

210
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:30,487
as compensation for sparing them
when coming across an unexpected enemy.

211
00:15:31,593 --> 00:15:36,292
Also, those who get information to
proceed favorably through later exams

212
00:15:36,364 --> 00:15:40,266
by providing the lacking scrolls to
comrades sharing the same village.

213
00:15:41,169 --> 00:15:45,105
And those who are thinking of,
under conditions favorable to them,

214
00:15:45,173 --> 00:15:48,939
annihilating the powerful ones who
will probably get through to the third exam.

215
00:15:49,877 --> 00:15:53,745
It goes without saying,
but these guys are quite the big guns

216
00:15:53,815 --> 00:15:56,545
and the worst enemies who
are definitely not conceited.

217
00:15:57,885 --> 00:15:58,817
I see.

218
00:15:59,554 --> 00:16:02,819
I understand the reason
why you appeared before us.

219
00:16:04,125 --> 00:16:06,059
You're scared, too, right?

220
00:16:07,362 --> 00:16:08,226
That's right.

221
00:16:16,971 --> 00:16:19,872
Now then, the tower has finally
come into view.

222
00:16:20,341 --> 00:16:21,774
From here on is the hard part.

223
00:16:21,943 --> 00:16:24,104
All right, let's go!

224
00:16:25,647 --> 00:16:26,739
An enemy already?

225
00:16:28,049 --> 00:16:28,743
There!

226
00:16:39,827 --> 00:16:42,091
Oh, it's just a centipede.

227
00:16:42,230 --> 00:16:43,993
Yikes! It's huge.

228
00:16:44,332 --> 00:16:46,163
All those legs are gross.

229
00:16:47,635 --> 00:16:48,602
Naruto.

230
00:16:48,903 --> 00:16:49,597
Huh?

231
00:16:49,871 --> 00:16:53,830
I'd like to avoid inadvertent sounds and
careless actions from here on.

232
00:16:54,075 --> 00:16:54,700
Huh?

233
00:16:55,109 --> 00:16:58,078
Rushing ahead through a dense forest
making noise like an elephant

234
00:16:58,146 --> 00:17:02,583
is the same as serving notice
in a loud voice that we're coming.

235
00:17:03,351 --> 00:17:05,717
We'd definitely receive
an enthusiastic welcome.

236
00:17:06,120 --> 00:17:08,486
O-Oh, I see.

237
00:17:09,724 --> 00:17:13,182
As long as time allows, we should
go slowly while remaining hidden.

238
00:17:13,461 --> 00:17:15,156
- Yeah.
- Okay.

239
00:17:15,263 --> 00:17:15,922
Sure.

240
00:17:25,873 --> 00:17:28,000
<i>Heh, not bad, everyone.</i>

241
00:17:37,952 --> 00:17:38,748
<i>Oh?</i>

242
00:17:48,329 --> 00:17:50,194
Okay, it's this way.

243
00:18:11,519 --> 00:18:12,679
Is it a trap?

244
00:18:13,221 --> 00:18:16,520
Yeah. It'll get intense ahead from here on.

245
00:18:36,210 --> 00:18:37,404
Kabuto!

246
00:18:40,948 --> 00:18:42,108
H-Huh?

247
00:18:42,383 --> 00:18:43,975
That was close, Naruto.

248
00:18:47,488 --> 00:18:48,887
Substitution Jutsu!

249
00:18:49,090 --> 00:18:52,821
I told you, it would get intense ahead
from here on.

250
00:18:59,834 --> 00:19:01,734
I've... had it...

251
00:19:02,370 --> 00:19:03,803
Oh! Sakura!

252
00:19:05,006 --> 00:19:06,633
For crying out loud,
how far have we walked?

253
00:19:07,608 --> 00:19:09,667
The tower hasn't gotten a bit closer.

254
00:19:11,212 --> 00:19:13,305
Here we can see it right
in front of our eyes.

255
00:19:13,481 --> 00:19:14,812
Strange...

256
